  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="8" style="v" />A drunken woman <char style="add">causes </char> great wrath;</para>
  <para style="q1">And she will not cover her own shame.</para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="9" style="v" />The whoredom of a woman is in the lifting up of her eyes;</para>
  <para style="q1">And it will be known by her eyelids.</para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="10" style="v" />Keep strict watch on a headstrong daughter,</para>
  <para style="q1">Lest she find liberty for herself, and use it.</para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="11" style="v" />Look well after an impudent eye;</para>
  <para style="q1">And marvel not if it trespass against you.</para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="12" style="v" />She will open her mouth, as a thirsty traveller,</para>
